quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  47,10,Have they not journeyed through the land and seen how was the end of those before them? God destroyed them; and for the misbelievers is the like thereof
  47,11,"That is because God is the patron of those who believe, and because the misbelievers have no patron"
  47,12,"Verily, God causes those who believe and do right to enter into gardens beneath which rivers flow; but those who misbelieve enjoy themselves and eat as the cattle eat; but the fire is the resort for them"
  47,13,"How many a city, stronger than thy city which has driven thee out, have we destroyed, and there was none to help them"
  47,14,"Is he who rests upon a manifest sign from his Lord like him, the evil of whose works is made seemly to him, and who follow their lusts"
  47,15,"The similitude of Paradise which is promised to the pious,- in it are rivers of water without corruption, and rivers of milk, the taste whereof changes not, and rivers of wine delicious to those who drink; and rivers of honey clarified; and there shall they have all kinds of fruit and forgiveness from their Lord! (Is that) like him who dwells in the fire for aye? and who are given to drink boiling water that shall rend their bowels asunder"
  47,16,"Some of them there are who listen to thee, until when they go forth from thee they say to those who have been given the knowledge, 'What is this which he says now?' These are those on whose hearts God his set a stamp and who follow their lusts"
  47,17,"But those who are guided, He guides them the more, and gives them the due of their piety"
  47,18,"Do they wait for aught but the Hour, that it should come to them suddenly? The conditions thereof have come already; how, when it has come on them, can they have their reminder"
  47,19,"Know thou that there is no god but God; and ask pardon for thy sin and for the believers, men and women; for God knows your return and your resort"
  47,20,"Those who misbelieve say, 'Why has not a surah been revealed?' but when a decisive surah is revealed and fighting is mentioned therein, thou mayest see those in whose heart is sickness looking towards thee with the look of one fainting in death"
  47,21,"Preferable for them were obedience and a reasonable speech! But when the matter is determined on, then if they believed God it were better for them"
  47,22,"Would ye perhaps, if ye had turned back, have done evil in the land and severed the bonds of kinship"
  47,23,"It is these whom God has cursed, and has made them deaf, and has blinded their eyesight"
  47,24,Do they not peruse the Qur'an? or are there locks upon their hearts
  47,25,"Verily, those who turn their backs after the guidance that has been manifested to them - Satan induces them, but (God) lets them go on for a time"
  47,26,"That is for that they say to those who are averse from what God has revealed, 'We will obey you in part of the affair!' but God knows their secrets"
  47,27,"How will it be when the angels take their souls, smiting their faces and their backs"
  47,28,This is because they follow what angers God and are averse from His goodwill; and their works are void
  47,29,Do those in whose hearts is sickness reckon that God will not bring their malice forth
  47,30,"But did we please we would show thee them, and thou shouldst know them by their cognisances. But thou shalt know them by their distorting their speech, and God knows their works"
  47,31,But we will try you until we know those among you who fight strenuously and the patient; and we will try the reports concerning you
  47,32,"Verily, those who misbelieve and turn folks off God's path, and break with the Apostle after the guidance that has been manifested to them, cannot harm God at all, and their works shall be void"